National Secretary of the Independent Petrol Marketers Association of Nigeria (IPMAN), Danladi Pasali on Saturday left his hospital bed where he has been recuperating from a gunshot wound to exercise his franchise. Pasali who is also the National Coordinator of the Buhari Campaign Organisation (BCO) was conveyed to his polling unit at Layin Ba’are in Jos north local government area of Plateau State in an ambulance and wearing a hospital gown. About 10 days ago, Pasali was ambushed by a group of armed robbers along Badeh road while returning to Jos from Abuja. Nigerians to buy kerosene at ‘lower price’ soon — IPMAN NNPC reforms will attract more investors – IPMAN Billions of unpaid waybills  threaten fuel supply – Marketers